<plot>This promotional short for _The Night of the Iguana (1964)_ (qv) focuses on how director 'John Huston (I)' (qv) puts his particular vision of a story on film. For this project, the cast and crew had to take a half-hour boat ride to get to the small village that Huston chose for location shooting. He studies the interaction between the actors to get the performances he wants. Several of the actors tell what it's like to be directed by Huston.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?411455</url></doc>
